subSubSection.paragraph:
First tergite (
Fig. 22
) 1.2 times as broad as long, less broadening posteriorly, scutum rugose and its margin finely crenulated. Second tergite transverse, 2.3 times as broad as long medially, antero-median field polished, laterally crenulated, otherwise rugose. Suture between tergites 2-3 straight, deep, crenulated. Tergites 3-5 with somewhat weakening rugosity, sixth tergite smooth. Ovipositor sheath long, as long as hind tibia + tarsomeres 1-4 combined.
